main event: A disc-shaped, red object the size of a grapefruit was observed for 10 minutes before disappearing behind a cloud cover in Iowa City, Iowa on April 5, 1966.
interesting points: Several people reported seeing the same object, which they believed to be a star that disappeared behind the cloud cover.
The object was disc-shaped, red in color, and about the size of a grapefruit.
The object was visible for 10 minutes before disappearing behind a cloud cover.
The report concludes that the sighting was likely an astro (star/planet) object.
There was no physical evidence or photographs of the sighting.
